follow in their privacy policies:

Information Collection: The app store may collect information about your device, such as your device type, operating system version, and unique device identifier. They may also collect information about your interactions with the app store, such as search queries and app downloads.

Information Use: The app store may use the information they collect to improve their services, provide personalized app recommendations, and analyze trends and usage patterns. They may also use your information to respond to your inquiries or to send you marketing communications.

Information Sharing: The app store may share your information with third-party service providers who help them operate their services. They may also share your information with app developers when you download their apps.

Security: The app store may implement security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access or disclosure.

Data Retention: The app store may retain your information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in their privacy policy.

It is important to read the privacy policies of any mobile app store you use and to understand how they collect, use, and share your data. If you have concerns about an app store's privacy practices, you can contact their customer support team or file a complaint with a relevant regulatory authority.
